textBody:
ICD may refer to:

In health and medicine:
* ICD, International Statistical Classification of Diseases and Related Health Problems
* Implantable cardioverter-defibrillator
* Impulse control disorder
* Intercostal drain
* Irritant contact dermatitis
* Isobaric counterdiffusion
 
Organizations:
* Information Control Division, a U.S. Army department in occupied Germany after World War II
* Short form of USAMRICD: the United States Army Medical Research Institute of Chemical Defense
* Iranian Club Dubai, a social club in Dubai, U.A.E.
* Islamic Corporation for the Development of the Private Sector

In technology:
* In-circuit debugger, in electronic hardware design
* MPLAB ICD, an in-circuit debugger by Microchip Technology
* Initial Capability Document, a description of system requirements used in United States Department of Defense
* Interface Control Document, in system engineering and software engineering
* Installable Client device driver, in Microsoft Windows

Other uses:
* Doctor of Canon Law, also "JCD", from Latin (Iuris Canonici Doctor)
* Incentive-centered design
* inland container depot
* Interatomic Coulombic Decay
